('reading', NULL, 101, 'Passage 11:\n\nRenewable energy sources, including solar, wind, hydroelectric, and geothermal power, are playing an increasingly important role in global energy production. Unlike fossil fuels, which are finite and produce greenhouse gases when burned, renewable energy sources are naturally replenished and generate little to no emissions during operation. This makes them crucial in efforts to combat climate change and reduce air pollution.\n\nSolar power harnesses energy from the sun using photovoltaic cells that convert sunlight directly into electricity. The cost of solar panels has decreased dramatically over the past decade, making solar energy increasingly competitive with conventional energy sources. Wind power, generated by turbines that capture kinetic energy from moving air, has also seen significant growth. Modern wind turbines can generate substantial amounts of electricity, especially when installed in areas with consistent wind patterns.\n\nDespite their benefits, renewable energy sources face certain challenges. Solar and wind power are intermittent—they only generate electricity when the sun is shining or the wind is blowing. This variability requires the development of energy storage systems, such as batteries, to ensure a stable power supply. Additionally, some renewable energy installations, particularly large wind farms and hydroelectric dams, can have environmental impacts on local ecosystems.\n\nWhat is the main advantage of renewable energy sources mentioned in the passage?', 'They are cheaper than all other energy sources', 'They are naturally replenished and produce little emissions', 'They require no infrastructure', 'They work in all weather conditions', 'b'),
